#
#             REPLACE <topic> WITH A SUITABLE ONE AS SUGGESTED BELOW.
#             Invent your own topic if needed.
#             Add a <scope> if necessary.
#             Be consistent.
#
# ----------- TOPICS THAT CHANGE THE SYMANTIC VERSION ---------------|
# feat!     : BREAKING CHANGES (increment MAJOR)
# feat      : non-breaking changes (increment MINOR)
# fix       : controlled fix (increment PATCH)
# hotfix    : hotfix (increment PATCH)
#
# ----------- TOPICS THAT DO NOT CHANGE THE SYMANTIC VERSION --------|
# build     : change build tooling or process
# chore     : unclassified commit
# doc       : change documentation
# meta      : change accompanying documentation like
#             README, CONTRIBUTE, CONDUCT, LICENSE, etc.
# perf      : change to performace profile
# refactor  : change to directory structures and/or file names
# style     : change file content only for style and idiomatic
# test      : introduce, modify or remove tests
# wip       : work in progress checkpoint
#             wip MUST have a <scope>
#
# ----------- END INSTRUCTIONS --------------------------------- >8 -|

